Well done to all at the Yogscast. It was the best yet I reckon. I know there’s been some changes this past year and I’m sad that they had to happen. But the current team are still just as fun to watch. I’ve been subbed for a while, sometime half way through the Jaffa series. It’s been nice seeing more of Simon again as well.

Keep being the Yogscast and we’ll be here to watch as always :)

That being said, I wouldn’t say no to a new MC series around a new (or even old) mod pack and would be great to see the Senate back in TTT.

All in all. A brilliant year and looking forward to another one to come.

All the best and thanks lads and lasses.

snippet.textDisplay:
Okay I enjoyed more this year than last year actually^^:
- Armchair admirals twice was very cool^^ (even though the second game was done ignoring the poll... I would have also liked Lewis's idea of just playing a bunch of different RTS games)
- Karaoke was top notch :)
- Drawing/Pen and Paper with Nina was short but very nice as always
- The Minecraft day was a great idea... sadly not much got done XD
- Pokemon was great but also too short... I get that Lydias and Harry's pokemon streams are so great because they don`t know the game but I think for a one of in the jingle jam they should get help from an expert for next year (I am sure there is at least one in the yogs)
- TABS was a great Idea for this Jingle Jam... no clue how the game holds up next year but 2019 it was a very nice suprise^^
- It was great to see so much from you Lewis^^, from Lydia and some of Spiff^^ maybe let him do an exploit next Year?... maybe even let him do a game where he plays against everyone else but he does an exploit! that would be amazing XD

the only things that I did not like or missed were:
- I missed TTT a bit but I get that it's hard to do because of so many people talking over each other and stuff...
- Cooking was a good Idea but badly executed... Hatfilms waste too much food and I was actually concerned about Lydias fingers when she attempted to cut 1 carrot for what seemed to be 5 minutes XD so next time please let someone remotely competent do the cooking XD PS: dont get me wrong I really love Lydia^^ best new Yogscast Creator!
- and the Alex the Rambler or "akward bros" stream was just too much for me... I have VERY VERY high tolerance for akwardness but I was not even suprised that Lewis had some kind of break down on that stream anymore... please don't do this to yourself again lewis... this is too much and it's actually not nice to either see you in pain or having a stream so akward that it hurts the viewer...

I really enjoyed 7 Days to die with colony crew, I think I've spent more time watching those than anything else. I think the blend of personalities in colony crew is spot on, I also enjoyed watching you play GTFO. I enjoyed the murder mystery, the high rollers streams and games nights, obviously the Civ V stream but also Civ VI with chatlof was great, I stayed up and watched the whole thing.

The all day minecraft stream with loads of different people was great too. There were so many good bits it's hard to pick just a few. I also just remembered the hearts of iron stream where Spiff just decided to invade America and forget about Germany, loads of laughs there. Pyrion's salt was hilarious. Keep it up, the only general feedback I can give you is more of the above and maybe slightly less TTT and GTA.
